THE FOUR DIMENSIONS
====================

  T = time       (universal — every record has sequence position)
  D = distance   (spatial, positional)
  M = mass       (content, amplitude, value)
  Q = charge     (category, type, polarity)

Every data type assigns meaning to D, M, Q. T is always time.

  text:   D=column,  M=line,     Q=section
  image:  D=x,       M=y,        Q=channel
  audio:  D=sample,  M=channel,  Q=frequency
  3D:     D=x,       M=y,        Q=z
  table:  D=row,     M=column,   Q=type
  tree:   D=depth,   M=sibling,  Q=type
  blob:   D=offset,  M=length,   Q=type

7 topologies. All ≤ 3 content dims + time = 4D. Can't exceed 4 —
Hurwitz theorem. Same reason: 4 forces, 4 DNA bases, 4 dimensions.

These 7 cover every sense (human, animal, machine):
  Pixels   (2D grid)   — vision, infrared, UV, polarized light
  Samples  (1D stream) — hearing, vestibular, magnetometer
  Frames   (3D volume) — echolocation, LIDAR, flow fields
  Text     (1D struct) — text, code, logs
  Table    (2D struct) — chemical, spectrometry, databases
  Tree     (hierarchy) — hierarchical, graph
  Blob     (raw)       — unstructured bytes

Each sense organ (biological or hardware) is a transducer:
read stimulus → transform → write to trace. A device walk IS an organ.


