TRACES
========

The only data structure. Everything is traces.

  trace layout (64 bytes, cache-line aligned):
    [0:7]   write cursor    (single writer — fermion)
    [8:15]  read cursor     (many readers — boson)
    [16:23] buffer address
    [24:31] depth (power of 2)
    [32:39] mask (depth - 1)
    [40:47] record size
    [48:63] reserved

Disk regions, RAM buffers, NVMe queues, network RDMA, GPU
command rings — all traces. Same bytes everywhere.

  ring record IS storage format IS wire format IS memory format.
  Zero translation.


STORAGE — DISK REGIONS AS TRACES
===================================

  DriveRegion:
    write_cursor  (allocation = advance cursor, one add bond)
    read_cursor   (reclamation = advance cursor, one add bond)
    base_lba, depth, mask, block_size, damping

  No block allocator. No bitmap. No filesystem.
  The trace primitive IS the allocator.

Damping = retention policy:
  drop:  overwrite oldest (data expires, ring rotates)
  block: stop writing (preserve everything)
  kick:  reject new writes (backpressure)

NVMe queues ARE traces. Submission queue = single-writer trace.
Completion queue = single-writer trace. Doorbell = write cursor.
NVMe is the lattice's native storage interface.

  disk access = trace access. ~1-2μs vs ~15-60μs VFS.

Direction: PIO ATA for testing → AHCI for SATA → NVMe for perf.


